column5: I'm supposed to be meeting him in Vaughan at 6.  I haven't heard from yet, and I really hope I didn't waste gas lol....

He was in the truck with me an hour ago as we crossed the border when he remembered. To make matters worse his cel was dead.. In any case there's no excuses for him, he should be tarred and feathered. I have his contact info if you need it.
Lol. He got a hold of me. I'm still at bps lol. He should be here soon
where is the report?  how was it?
I just walked in the door.  (was amazing, some large powerful fish today)
Eagerly awaiting with intense Envy!!!   Is it mainly a fall run down there?...this is what I have heard.
Here's a teaser. It may not be where you think:
Looks like Niagara, NICE Fishy...looks kinda bruised
Great day boys - I thoroughly enjoyed that!!!  Here's another taste.   Unfortunately for us, most of the bigger fish won the battles today!
Nice shoulders on that hen,...just curious do you guys have jobs?  lol...are you milking the H1N1 thingy...lol,..just kidding!!!
Just a stab,...looks like it with those rocks current and mist.
Sometimes it pays to take a well-timed day off...this was one of them!
you have non fishing plans tomm........or it was on the list
I think *hack! hack!* I must be coming down with H1N1... Might.... have to.... take the day off tomorrow....    p.-
